    "result": "W",
    "boxscore_url": "https://www.brownbears.com/sports/baseball/stats/2026/yale/boxscore/20366",
    "recap_url": "https://www.brownbears.com/news/2026/3/22/reids-domination-leads-baseball-to-series-win-over-yale",
    "recap_headline": "Brown University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "WEST HAVEN, Conn. \u2013\nSenior pitcher\nDylan Reid\ndominated over 7.0 shutout innings to lead the Brown baseball team to a big 8-0 shutout win at Yale on Sunday. The win gives Brown (7-10, 2-1 Ivy)\u00a0a series win over the Bulldogs (9-8, 1-2 Ivy) for the first time since 2016 and is the first series win to open Ivy League play since 2018.\nReid delivered a career performance, controlling the game for 7.0 shutout innings, allowing just three hits and three walks with eight strikeouts, all against a Yale team that entered the weekend leading the Ivy League with a .276 batting average. He threw 72 of his 103 pitches for strikes and had the out-pitch throughout, inducing a double play to end the fifth, picking off a runner to end the sixth inning, and got a big strikeout after an error to end the seventh.\nSince the second inning of game two of Saturday's doubleheader, the Bears have not allowed a run in the last 17 innings.\nWe love pickoffs! Reid's domination continues \ud83d\udc4a\nWatch on ESPN+\npic.twitter.com/zXSlYsjS8Q\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nBrown grinded out at bats and throughout the game, scoring seven of their eight runs with two outs. Sophomore\nAlex Benevento\nled the way with three hits and an RBI. Junior\nBrady Dever\nreached base four times with two hits, two walks, and scored two runs with one RBI. Freshman\nMatt Luigs\nwent 2-for-4 with a walk and three RBIs. Senior\nMika Petersen\nalso drove in two runs.\nBrown jumped in front with a pair of runs in the third inning. With runners on second and third with one out,\nMark Henshon\nhad an RBI ground out and Benevento lined an RBI single down the right field line.\nRBI knock for Benevento tacks on another for the 2-0 lead in the 3rd!\nWatch on ESPN+\npic.twitter.com/6a9S5eSN9V\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nThe Bears doubled the lead in the top of the fourth when\nChristian Butera\nand Dever drew walks. Luigs stopped up with two outs and drove an outside pitch to the opposite field and over the head of the right fielder for a two-run triple to make it 4-0.\nLuigs doubles the lead in the fourth...takes the pitch the other way for a 2-run triple!\nM4 | 4-0 Brown\nWatch on ESPN+\npic.twitter.com/GESaqSlE9g\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nThree more runs in the fifth pushed the lead to 7-0 as Petersen roped a two-out double off the wall in right field to knock in two runs, and Luigs later drew a bases loaded walk.\nMore two-out magic! Five of the six runs have come with two outs as Mika drives the 0-2 pitch off the wall to plate two more runs!\nWatch on ESPN+\npic.twitter.com/531OtbL6HL\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nDever added some more insurance in the ninth with an RBI single.\nGrind-it-out at bat for Dever ends with an RBI knock!\n8-0 Bears in the 9th\nWatch on ESPN+\npic.twitter.com/tMDifUv8Mz\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nThe Bears will return home on Tuesday afternoon, March 24 to host Stonehill in a non-league matchup. First pitch is set for 3 p.m. on ESPN+.\nGallery:\n(3-22-2026) Baseball at Yale, 3/22/2026\nBROWN UNIVERSITY SPORTS FOUNDATION\nThe Brown University Sports Foundation (BUSF) is the backbone of our athletics program, playing a crucial role in enhancing the student-athlete experience.\u00a0This\u00a0is possible through philanthropic support from our alumni, parents, fans, and friends.\u00a0Your\u00a0gift through the Sports Foundation can immediately impact today's Brown Bears, helping them excel in the classroom, in competition, and, most importantly, in the community. Please click\nhere\nto learn more about how\u00a0you\u00a0can support the Bears.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Brown Athletics, please follow\n@BrownU_Bears\non X and\n@BrownU_Bears\non Instagram. Like\nBrownUBears\non Facebook and subscribe to the\nBrownAthletics\nYouTube channel.",
